                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.01/170: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Personal Representative of the President in India</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-27T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 27, 1942—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>162. Your no. 208, April 21, 6 p.m. Aside from the time element involved in
                    consulting with the British and Chinese Governments, a <pb facs="0657" n="645"
                        xml:id="pg_645"/> joint statement of Pacific war aims at this time would
                    raise a number of complex problems relating to the future of many Oriental
                    peoples. Such problems, of course, would require the careful consideration of
                    all the United Nations with interests in the Pacific area and a mutual
                    understanding among them as to the solution of these problems.</p>
                <p>There is, furthermore, inherent danger in the adoption by this Government of
                    measures which might appear to favor unduly a particular faction in India. It is
                    our view that this Government will continue to retain the confidence of all
                    Indian groups only if it continues to adhere to a policy of strict impartiality
                    among them.</p>
                <p>In this connection you will, of course, wish to be careful not to identify
                    yourself too closely with any particular group or groups in Indian national
                    life.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
